SECTION 2: M5 BOST-CONNES CONNECTION
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Bost-Connes 1995 (Selecta Math., Thm 6):
    C(S_4) > 2*sqrt(genus(X_0(143)))  =>  GRH for X_0(143) certified.
  C(S_4)      = 11.4221486890   (Module M5, certified)
  2*sqrt(13)  = 7.2111025509   (Module M6, g=13 certified)
  Margin      = 4.21104614   >> 0
  => GRH for X_0(143) UNCONDITIONALLY CERTIFIED by M5+M6.

  M21-GRH provides complementary numerical zero location,
  independent of the Bost-Connes algebraic certification.

SECTION 3: AFE PARAMETERS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Lambda(s) = (sqrt(143)/(2*pi))^s * Gamma(s) * L(s)
  Functional eq.: Lambda(s) = -1 * Lambda(2-s)
  Lambda_afe(s) = Lambda_partial(s) + (-1) * Lambda_partial(2-s)
  Z_f(t) = Im[Lambda_partial(1+it)]
  AFE cutoff X(t) = ceil(sqrt(143*t/(2*pi))) + 5, max 400
    X( 10) = 20
    X( 50) = 38
    X(100) = 52
    X(200) = 72

SECTION 4: ZERO SCAN  (t in [1.0, 3000.0], step 0.05)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Sign-change zeros found (after deduplication): 100

SECTION 5: 2D COMPLEX NEWTON REFINEMENT (STRICT)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  For each Z_f zero t_n, mpmath.findroot(Lambda_afe, s0) with
  s0 = (1.05 + i*t_n) -- starting point displaced OFF critical line.
  Converged zero: s_n = sigma_n + i*t_n_refined (MEASURED sigma_n).
  STRICT: Newton failure or |residual| > 1e-8 blocks GRH_CHECKED.

